(a) The repeal of any statute creating, defining or relating to any criminal offense set forth under the laws of this State, shall not have the effect of releasing or extinguishing any penalty, forfeiture or liability incurred under such statute,
§

 1;

When used for the purpose of describing or requiring a sentence of incarceration imposed pursuant to this title, the terms “minimum,” “mandatory,” “minimum mandatory” and “mandatory minimum” shall be construed as being synonymous.71 Del. Laws, c. 98,
